body: Hello, seems related to issues #255 and #210 (and here: https://forum.image.sc/t/how-can-i-solve-this-problem-importerror-hdfstore-requires-pytables/22555) Namely, seems your installation of pytables is not correct. **Question 1:** correct, you cannot run the same code again as it is trying to create a new project again. If you want to set a variable, just simply type: 
```
config_path = r'D:\Deeplabcut\xg-Lx-2019-05-04\config.yaml' 
```
--> please follow the formatting guide here: https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/blob/master/docs/UseOverviewGuide.md#configure-the-project

**Question2:** seems your kernel died, but doesn't seem related to DLC? I would recommend just using the supplied env and use ipython to run the code. 

**Question3:** Yes, you need to use conda to install pytables, not pip. The easiest is to just use our anaconda environment, not your pytorch environment (py36-pytorch): https://github.com/AlexEMG/DeepLabCut/tree/master/conda-environments
